race.comment: LARADO (1) resumes here but the form he showed in his first preparation was good enough for a race of this calibre. Tuned up for this with a recent trial and a strong showing while fresh would not surprise. Former Victorian TARA'S REWARD (4) returned in good order winning over this track and trip in the first run for the new barn and successful rider Thornton sticks in the irons. Can go back-to-back. HANNABANA (7) has a handy record here on her home circuit with a win and two placings from four spins. Strips fitter second-up and has genuine top-three prospects. CALL TO COURAGE (9) shed the maiden tag last time out and will have derived a stack of confidence from that outing. In the mix. DRANITZELLE (2) best of the rest while fresh.
